<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 06 at 11:52AM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Cherokee, southeastern Gordon, western Pickens and northeastern
Bartow Counties through 1230 PM EDT...
At 1152 AM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Fairmount, or 14 miles
east of Calhoun, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Talking Rock, Fairmount, Ranger, Salacoa Valley, Blaine, Talmadge,
Funkhouser, and Hinton.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
